---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="VS Code Extension" description="Install and configure the physure Meta-Lang (MKML) support in VS Code" activeSection="vscode">
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="kicker">Extensions</div>
    <h1>VS Code Extension</h1>
    <p>Get native support for the <strong>physure Meta-Lang (MKML)</strong> syntax in Visual Studio Code, Cursor, and VSCodium.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="callout callout-info" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; padding: 1.25rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--accent); border-radius: var(--radius-sm);">
    <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.5;"><strong>Manual Installation Pack:</strong></p>
    <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <a href="/vsc-measurekit-0.1.0.vsix" download class="btn-primary" style="margin: 0;">Download vsc-measurekit-0.1.0.vsix</a>
      <span style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">(Compatible with VS Code 1.93.0+)</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Key Features ✨</h2>
  <div class="features-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>🎨 Semantic Highlighting</h3>
      <p>Robust syntax coloring for variables, physical units, exponents, uncertainties (<code>+/-</code> or <code>±</code>), conversion operators (<code>=&gt;</code>), and assertions (<code>==</code>).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>⚡ Rapid Execution</h3>
      <p>Instantly run the active <code>.mkml</code> file using your configured Python interpreter context with a single keyboard shortcut.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>💬 Interactive REPL</h3>
      <p>Start an interactive terminal REPL and stream the current line or active code selections to it dynamically.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>🔍 Unit Autocomplete</h3>
      <p>Intelligent autocomplete lists querying active physical units live from your configured Python <code>physure</code> installation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>ℹ️ Hover Info & Outline</h3>
      <p>Hover a unit to see its base dimensions/description, or jump to any assigned variable using the built-in Document Outline.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>🛠️ Inline Diagnostics</h3>
      <p>Get instant notifications about unbalanced parentheses and unrecognized syntax characters as you type.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Installation Methods</h2>

  <h3>1. VSIX Manual Installation (Recommended)</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Download the <a href="/vsc-measurekit-0.1.0.vsix" download>vsc-measurekit-0.1.0.vsix</a> extension package.</li>
    <li>In VS Code or Cursor, open the Command Palette (<code>Ctrl+Shift+P</code> or <code>Cmd+Shift+P</code>).</li>
    <li>Select <strong>Extensions: Install from VSIX...</strong>.</li>
    <li>Navigate to the downloaded <code>.vsix</code> file and select it.</li>
    <li>Reload the editor window if prompted.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>2. Developer Symbolic Link (Local Link)</h3>
  <p>If you have cloned the extension repository, you can symlink it directly to your editor's extension folder:</p>
  
  <div class="tabs">
    <div class="tab-list">
      <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="sym-vscode">VS Code / Cursor</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="sym-codium">VSCodium</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel active" id="sym-vscode">
      <pre><code># Linux / macOS
ln -s "/path/to/vsc_physure" ~/.vscode/extensions/vsc-measurekit</code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel" id="sym-codium">
      <pre><code># Linux / macOS
ln -s "/path/to/vsc_physure" ~/.vscode-oss/extensions/vsc-measurekit</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Keyboard Shortcuts ⌨️</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Action</th>
        <th>Linux / Windows</th>
        <th>macOS</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Run Current MKML File</strong></td>
        <td><code>Ctrl + Alt + N</code></td>
        <td><code>Cmd + Alt + N</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Send Selection/Line to REPL</strong></td>
        <td><code>Shift + Enter</code></td>
        <td><code>Shift + Enter</code></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Configuration ⚙️</h2>
  <p>The extension requires a Python interpreter containing the <code>physure</code> library to enable unit autocompletions and script execution. By default, it traverses directories upwards from the current file looking for a virtual environment (<code>.venv</code>).</p>
  
  <p>You can customize the interpreter executable path directly in the settings:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Open the editor settings (<code>Ctrl+,</code> or <code>Cmd+,</code>).</li>
    <li>Search for <strong>physure</strong>.</li>
    <li>Configure the <strong>Python Path</strong> option.</li>
  </ol>
  
  <p>Alternatively, configure it inside your project's local <code>.vscode/settings.json</code>:</p>
  <pre><code>&#123;
  "vsc-measurekit.pythonPath": "/path/to/your/project/.venv/bin/python"
&#125;</code></pre>

  <div class="next-section">
    <a href="/changelog" class="btn-primary">Next: Changelog →</a>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  .card {
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }
  .card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    transition: background 0.2s;
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent2);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .next-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.tab-list').forEach(tabList => {
    const tabs = tabList.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn');
    tabs.forEach(tab => {
      tab.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const targetId = tab.getAttribute('data-tab');
        tabs.forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
        tab.classList.add('active');
        const container = tabList.closest('.tabs');
        container?.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel').forEach(panel => {
          panel.classList.toggle('active', panel.id === targetId);
        });
      });
    });
  });
</script>
